  "datePublished": "2026-01-01",
  "description": "Consent in [role-playing games](../index.md) is agreement among players about what content is acceptable in play. Unlike many other forms of entertainment, role-playing games are co-created in real time — any participant can introduce themes, scenarios, or situations that others find uncomfortable or harmful. Consent practices address this by making boundaries explicit and revisable.",
